        "story_version_id": "01JCYVER000000000000001",
        "story_id": "01JCYSTORY00000000000001",
        "body_markdown": "# City Council Approves Budget Amendment for Riverside Park\n\nThe Riverside City Council voted 7-2 on Tuesday to approve a $2.3 million budget amendment for the renovation of Riverside Park. The amendment allocates funds for new playground equipment, walking trails, and stormwater management improvements.\n\nThe funding comes from a combination of federal infrastructure grants ($1.5M) and the city's capital improvement fund ($800K). Construction is expected to begin in spring 2027.\n\nCouncil members Maria Rodriguez and David Kim cast the dissenting votes, citing concerns about the timeline and the impact on other capital projects.\n\nThe total project cost was initially reported as $3.1 million, but the final approved amount was $2.3 million after value engineering reduced the scope.",
        "disclosure_markdown": "Reporter's spouse works for the parks department.",
        "created_at": "2026-06-01T14:00:00Z"
      }
    ],
